# ASTU . BOAP . SEM-II . Course Work repo

## General

### Show help

Show application description, version, author information and command list.

```sh
markforge --help
```

### Show version

Display application version.

```sh
markforge --version
```

---

## Database Commands

### Initialize example database

Create table in interactive mode

```sh
markforge db --init
```

Show available table templates list

```sh
markforge db --init --templates
```

Create application database with example schema and demo data.

```sh
markforge db --init --template <employees|students>
```

Delete table with `<table_name>`

```sh
markforge db --drop <table_name>
```

Delete all tables

```sh
markforge db --drop --all
```

Show user created tables

```sh
markforge db --list
```

Show all tables

```sh
markforge db --list --all
```

### Show schema

Display `<table_name>` database schema

```sh
markforge db --schema-show <table_name>
```

---

## Person / Record Commands

### List records

Show all records in interactive mode:

```sh
markforge data --show
```

Show specific records in `<table_name>`:

```sh
markforge data --show <table_name>
```

---

## Template Commands

### List templates

Show available templates:

```sh
markforge template --list
```

Show template `<template_name>`:

```sh
markforge template --show <template_name>
```

Register template to use inline:

```sh
markforge template --add </path/to/><filename>.<txt|md|docx> -as <template_name>
```

Remove template:

```sh
markforge template --remove <template_name>
```

---

## Document Generation

Generate document with `<template_name>` as template source

```sh
markforge generate --source <table_name> --template <template_name>
```

Generate documents for all records.

Output directory

```sh
markforge generate --source <table_name> --template <template_name> --output </path/to/output/>
```

Specify custom output directory.

---

Supported Template Formats

* TXT
* Markdown (MD)
* DOCX
* XLS
* XLSX

Planned support:

* PDF import
* ODT
* HTML

---

Examples

```sh
markforge db init
```

```sh
markforge data list
```

```sh
markforge generate \
```

    --template invitation \
    --id 3
```sh
markforge generate \
```

    --template report \
    --all

